Subject: [PATCH] ec: Fix endianness in hash_to_curve

The big_endian_to_words function in hash_to_curve.cc assumes
little-endian byte layout within BN_ULONG words when converting
big-endian byte arrays to word arrays.

On big-endian systems, the byte indexing needs to be adjusted
using the XOR pattern to account for word-level endianness.

Based on the Chromium big-endian patches by Marcus Comstedt.
---
 crypto/ec/hash_to_curve.cc | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/crypto/ec/hash_to_curve.cc b/crypto/ec/hash_to_curve.cc
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/crypto/ec/hash_to_curve.cc
+++ b/crypto/ec/hash_to_curve.cc
@@ -162,7 +162,11 @@ void big_endian_to_words(BN_ULONG *out, size_t num_words, const uint8_t *in,
   OPENSSL_memset(out, 0, num_words * sizeof(BN_ULONG));
   uint8_t *out_u8 = (uint8_t *)out;
   for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++) {
+#ifdef OPENSSL_BIGENDIAN
+    out_u8[(len - 1 - i) ^ (sizeof(BN_ULONG) - 1)] = in[i];
+#else
     out_u8[len - 1 - i] = in[i];
+#endif
   }
 }

